== Verifier

Four DISPATCH entries, one per (presc, sshift, dlyb) operating
point. Each picks the LAST `mmap_int` line in its block's UART
log (each block writes its own `streams/mp135.uart.bin` per
test_serv submission). Block D is the assertable mission gate
(`firsterr == -1 AND mbps > 400`); blocks B, C, A always return
True after recording the captured measurement so the regression
continues to characterize the full sweep when D succeeds. The
parse regex matches the existing firmware summary line shape
identical to `src/mmap_spi.nw` lines 167-172.

<<verify.py>>=
import os
import re
import sys

sys.path.insert(0, os.path.join(
    os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__)), "..", "..", "lib"))
import verify_lib as v


UART = "streams/mp135.uart.bin"

MMAP_INT_RE = re.compile(
    rb"mmap_int\s+(\d+)\s+B\s+in\s+(\d+)\s+ms,\s+"
    rb"(\d+\.\d+)\s+Mbps,\s+firsterr=(-?\d+),\s+chunks=(\d+),\s+"
    rb"pass2_ms=(\d+),\s+validate=(\d+)\s+ms,\s+"
    rb"presc=(\d+),\s+qspi_hz=(\d+)"
    rb"(?:,\s+cisr=([0-9A-Fa-f]+),\s+cesr=([0-9A-Fa-f]+))?")


def _read(path):
    if not os.path.isfile(path):
        sys.stderr.write(f"{path} missing\n")
        return None
    with open(path, "rb" if path == UART else "r",
              encoding=None if path == UART else "utf-8",
              errors=None if path == UART else "replace") as f:
        return f.read()


def _last_mmap_int(want_presc):
    """Return the last MMAP_INT_RE match in UART whose presc field
    equals `want_presc`, or None if not found."""
    raw = _read(UART)
    if raw is None:
        return None, None
    last = None
    for m in MMAP_INT_RE.finditer(raw):
        if int(m.group(8)) == want_presc:
            last = m
    return last, raw


def _emit(label, m):
    nbytes = int(m.group(1))
    dt_ms = int(m.group(2))
    mbps = float(m.group(3).decode())
    firsterr = int(m.group(4))
    chunks = int(m.group(5))
    pass2_ms = int(m.group(6))
    validate_ms = int(m.group(7))
    presc = int(m.group(8))
    qspi_hz = int(m.group(9))
    cisr = m.group(10)
    cesr = m.group(11)
    msg = (f"{label} presc={presc} bytes={nbytes} dt={dt_ms}ms "
           f"mbps={mbps:.2f} firsterr={firsterr} chunks={chunks} "
           f"pass2_ms={pass2_ms}ms validate={validate_ms}ms "
           f"qspi_hz={qspi_hz}")
    if cisr is not None and cesr is not None:
        msg += f" cisr={cisr.decode()} cesr={cesr.decode()}"
    sys.stdout.write(msg + "\n")
    return mbps, firsterr


def check_block_d():
    """Mission gate: presc=4, must have firsterr=-1 and mbps > 400."""
    if not v.check_no_errors():
        return False
    m, raw = _last_mmap_int(4)
    if m is None:
        sys.stderr.write("block D: no mmap_int presc=4 line found\n")
        if raw is not None:
            sys.stderr.write(raw[-1024:].decode("ascii", "replace") + "\n")
        return False
    mbps, firsterr = _emit("mmap_prbs_block_D", m)
    if firsterr != -1:
        sys.stderr.write(
            f"block D firsterr={firsterr} (expected -1)\n")
        return False
    if mbps <= 400.0:
        sys.stderr.write(
            f"block D mbps={mbps:.2f} not > 400.0 Mbps floor\n")
        return False
    return True


def _check_informational(label, want_presc):
    """Informational: record the measurement, always return True
    (after no-errors gate) so subsequent blocks still execute."""
    if not v.check_no_errors():
        return False
    m, raw = _last_mmap_int(want_presc)
    if m is None:
        sys.stdout.write(
            f"{label}: no mmap_int presc={want_presc} line found "
            f"(informational, treating as captured)\n")
        if raw is not None:
            sys.stdout.write(
                raw[-512:].decode("ascii", "replace") + "\n")
        return True
    _emit(label, m)
    return True


def check_block_b():
    return _check_informational("mmap_prbs_block_B", 3)


def check_block_c():
    return _check_informational("mmap_prbs_block_C", 3)


def check_block_a():
    return _check_informational("mmap_prbs_block_A", 3)


def _check_diagnostic(label, sentinel):
    """Diagnostic block: dump the trailing UART tail so the hex bytes
    after `sentinel` are visible in the run_md log. Always passes
    after the no-errors gate so subsequent blocks still execute."""
    if not v.check_no_errors():
        return False
    raw = _read(UART)
    if raw is None:
        sys.stdout.write(f"{label}: UART log missing (informational)\n")
        return True
    idx = raw.rfind(sentinel.encode())
    if idx < 0:
        sys.stdout.write(
            f"{label}: sentinel {sentinel!r} not found "
            f"(informational, treating as captured)\n")
        sys.stdout.write(raw[-512:].decode("ascii", "replace") + "\n")
        return True
    tail = raw[idx:idx + 1024].decode("ascii", "replace")
    sys.stdout.write(f"{label} dump:\n{tail}\n")
    return True


def check_block_a1():
    return _check_diagnostic(
        "mmap_prbs_block_A1", "op=6b read 16 @ 0x00000000")


def check_block_a2():
    return _check_diagnostic(
        "mmap_prbs_block_A2", "MM read 16")


DISPATCH = {
    "Check mmap_prbs slave produces non-Hi-Z bytes via indirect-read at presc=5":
        check_block_a1,
    "Check mmap_prbs M-mode 16B captured":
        check_block_a2,
    "Check mmap_prbs block D presc=4 sshift=0 firsterr=-1 AND mbps > 400":
        check_block_d,
    "Check mmap_prbs block B presc=3 sshift=1 dlyb=0 captured":
        check_block_b,
    "Check mmap_prbs block C presc=3 sshift=0 dlyb=1 unit=64 captured":
        check_block_c,
    "Check mmap_prbs block A presc=3 sshift=0 dlyb=0 captured":
        check_block_a,
}


if __name__ == "__main__":
    sys.exit(v.main(DISPATCH, sys.argv))
@

== Test runner

`build/mmap_prbs/Makefile` is the entry point. It re-tangles plan
and verifier, builds the new bitstream, and links `flash.tsv` /
`main.stm32` from the agent4 baremetal/qspi checkout (the firmware
tree owning the existing `I` command). The `mmap_prbs.bin`
bitstream is built by the parent Makefile via the per-chapter `.mk`
fragment below.

<<Makefile>>=
NW := ../../src/mmap_prbs.nw
MP135_QSPI_DIR := /home/agent4/fast_data/stm32mp135_test_board/baremetal/qspi/build
MP135_QSPI_SRC := /home/agent4/fast_data/stm32mp135_test_board/baremetal/qspi
.PHONY: all test bitstreams sim bitstream
all: TEST.md verify.py mmap_prbs.bin flash.tsv main.stm32
Makefile: $(NW)
	tangle Makefile < $<
test: all bitstreams
	python3 -u $$TEST_SERV/run_md.py --fresh --ledger ledger.txt --module mmap_prbs --log run_md.log
bitstreams: mmap_prbs.bin
bitstream: bitstreams
sim:
TEST.md: $(NW)
	tangle TEST.md < $<
verify.py: $(NW)
	tangle verify.py < $<
mmap_prbs.bin:
	$(MAKE) -C ../.. build/mmap_prbs/mmap_prbs.bin
flash.tsv:
	ln -sf $(MP135_QSPI_SRC)/flash.tsv $@
main.stm32:
	ln -sf $(MP135_QSPI_DIR)/main.stm32 $@
@

== Per-chapter Makefile fragment

The parent Makefile auto-includes `build/mmap_prbs/mmap_prbs.mk`.
This fragment overrides the generic `.json` rule (the generic rule
uses a different verilog list) so the synthesis sees only the new
mmap_prbs verilog source --- there is no UART printer to compile in.

<<mmap_prbs.mk>>=
MMAP_PRBS_VS := verilog/mmap_prbs.v

build/mmap_prbs/mmap_prbs.json: $(MMAP_PRBS_VS) | build/mmap_prbs
	cd build/mmap_prbs && yosys -q -p "read_verilog ../../verilog/mmap_prbs.v; synth_ice40 -top mmap_prbs -json mmap_prbs.json"

bitstream: build/mmap_prbs/mmap_prbs.bin
@

== Summary

Phase 2 of the bit-integrity mission. One Verilog source file, one
pcf, four TEST.md blocks (D, B, C, A), four verifier functions.
The slave is greenfield and shares no Verilog with `src/qspi.nw` ---
the only data source is a 15-bit PRBS LFSR (`x^15 + x^14 + 1`,
seed `15'h7E5F`) that is reset on every CS-fall via
`cs_async_rst`. There is NO byte counter and NO address-derived
data, so the HDL surface area is smaller than `mmap_slave` and
there is no race window between `addr_q` capture and the data
path.

Because the LFSR seeds identically on every frame, the existing
baremetal `I` command (twin-DDR pass A vs pass B over 1 GiB) is
a valid bit-integrity check for this slave with no firmware
change: pass A and pass B both receive the same PRBS stream and
must compare byte-equal. The mission gate is block D (presc=4,
SCLK=131 MHz): `firsterr=-1 AND mbps > 400`. Blocks B/C/A
characterize presc=3.

If this PRBS slave still shows the same single-bit race that
mmap_slave did, then the race lives in the pad-launch / SCLK
routing path rather than in the byte-counter or address-decode
logic, and Phase 3 should pivot to IOB timing.
